Display directory structure description

Please follow below rules to arrange your drivers,
all driver files should be put into the correct folder.

Directory tree overview:

display/
├── dpu
|   ├── cmdlist
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist.c
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist.h
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_frame_mgr.c
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_frame_mgr.h
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_node.c
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_node.h
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_util.c
|   |   ├── dpu_cmdlist_common.h
│   |   └── ...
│   ├── dp
│   │   ├── dp_drm.h
│   │   ├── dp_drm.c
│   │   ├── dp_display_drv.c
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── dsi
│   │   ├── dsi_drm.h
│   │   ├── dsi_drm.c
│   │   ├── dsi_display_drv.c
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── hw
│   │   ├── hw_ops
│   │   │   ├── hw_reg
│   │   │   │   ├── dpu_hw_xxx_reg.h
│   │   │   │   └── ...
│   │   │   ├── dpu_hw_xxx_ops.h
│   │   │   ├── dpu_hw_xxx_ops.c
│   │   │   └── ...
│   │   ├── dpu_hw_common.h
│   │   ├── dpu_hw_xxx.c
│   │   ├── dpu_hw_xxx.h
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── Kconfig
│   ├── Makefile
│   ├── dpu_drv.c
│   ├── dpu_drv.h
│   └── ...
├── dsi_fpga
│   ├── dsi_display_drv.c
│   └── ...
├── veu
│   ├── veu_drv.c
│   └── ...
├── Kconfig
└── Makefile

Detailed descriptions of every path:

display/
 - First level folder, all display related modules will be
   put into this folder, include DPU DLKM driver, VEU DLKM
   driver, dsi_test DLKM driver and so on.
 - DLKM: Dynamically Loadable Kernel Modules.

display/dpu/
 - DPU driver folder, include all dpu related core frameworks,
   utils, and the detailed dpu drm driver.
 - Naming rule: dpu_xxx.h, dpu_xxx.c

display/dpu/dp/
 - DP display related framework and driver folder.
 - Naming rule: dp_xxx.h, dp_xxx.c

display/dpu/dsi/
 - DSI display related framework and driver folder.
 - Naming rule: dsi_xxx.h, dsi_xxx.c

display/dpu/hw/
 - DPU hardware related folder, the hardware abstract layer
   of dpu hardware modules will be put into this folder.
 - Naming rule: dpu_hw_xxx.h, dpu_hw_xxx.c
 - File rule:
   - dpu_hw_common.h: the common structure, enum and
     macro definition which be used by both low level
     and high level layers or will be used by two modules
     should be put intothis file.

display/dpu/hw/hw_ops/
 - The detailed low level drivers of every dpu hardware
   module will be put into this folder.
 - Naming rule: dpu_hw_xxx_ops.h, dpu_hw_xxx_ops.c

display/dpu/hw/hw_ops/hw_reg/
 - The auto-generated header file of dpu registers will
   be put into this folder.
 - Naming rule: dpu_hw_xxx_reg.h

display/dsi_fpga/
 - DSI fpga driver folder, include the dsi fpga driver
   and the detailed phy driver for fpga testing purpose.
 - Naming rule: dsi__xxx.h, dsi_xxx.c

display/veu/
 - VEU driver folder, include all veu driver related
   framework and driver.
 - Naming rule: veu_xxx.h, veu_xxx.c

display/dpu/cmdlist/
 - cmdlist module folder, include all cmdlist module related
   framework.
 - Naming rule: dpu_cmdlist_xxx.h, dpu_cmdlist_xxx.c

 display/xplayer
 - wfd xplayer driver folder, include all wfd interaction
   related framework.
 - Naming rule: xplayer_xxx.h, xplayer_xxx.c
